        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 5:03PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Villa Grove, or 48 miles north of Alamosa, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Heavy rain and Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
This heavy rain is falling on the steep western slopes of
the Sangre de Cristo mountains.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Villa Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
